
[1]hydraulics

   HYDRAUL'ICS, n. The science of the motion and force of fluids, and of
   the construction of all kinds of instruments and machines by which the
   force of fluids is applied to practical purposes; a branch of
   hydrostatic.

   Hydraulics is that branch of the science of hydrodynamics which treats
   of fluids considered as in motion.
